  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good Android apps for learning guitar (for beginners)?",
  "response": "Learning guitar as a beginner can be both exciting and challenging, and there are several Android apps that can help you through this journey. Here are some popular and well-regarded apps:\n\n1. **Yousician**:\n   - **Features**: Interactive lessons, real-time feedback, a huge library of songs, video tutorials.\n   - **Best for**: Self-paced learning with instant feedback.\n\n2. **Justin Guitar**:\n   - **Features**: Structured course by renowned guitar teacher Justin Sandercoe, video lessons, practice routines.\n   - **Best for**: Comprehensive and practical learning method.\n\n3. **GuitarTuna**:\n   - **Features**: Accurate tuner, metronome, chords library, songbook with easy-to-follow tabs.\n   - **Best for**: Keeping your guitar in tune and practicing rhythm.\n\n4. **Fender Play**:\n   - **Features**: Step-by-step instruction, high-quality video lessons, song tutorials.\n   - **Best for**: Beginner to early intermediate players, with a structured learning path.\n\n5. **Ultimate Guitar: Chords & Tabs**:\n   - **Features**: Huge database of chords, tabs, and lyrics for thousands of songs, interactive features like Tonebridge.\n   - **Best for**: Learning to play songs and expanding your repertoire.\n\n6. **AmpliTube**:\n   - **Features**: Guitar and bass effects, virtual amplifiers, customizable setup.\n   - **Best for**: Experimenting with different sounds and effects.\n\n7. **Simply Guitar by JoyTunes**:\n   - **Features**: Immediate feedback, engaging lessons, beginner-friendly approach.\n   - **Best for**: Real-time feedback and interactive learning.\n\n8. **Chordify**:\n   - **Features**: Automatically extracts chords from your favorite songs, visual representation of chords.\n   - **Best for**: Learning chords of popular songs quickly.\n\n9. **TrueFire**:\n   - **Features**: Video lessons, guided learning paths, jam tracks, song libraries.\n   - **Best for**: Diverse styles and techniques from professional guitarists.\n\n10. **CoachGuitar**:\n    - **Features**: No musical theory needed, color-coded method, video tutorials.\n    - **Best for**: Learn by visualizing finger placement without needing to read music.\n\nThese apps can provide you with various tools and methods to make learning guitar more accessible and enjoyable. It often helps to try a few and see which app\u2019s approach resonates best with your learning style.",
